The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing a set of images from multi-view measurements, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The proposed method involves modeling the observed images as a sum of background and foreground images, and estimating the transformation parameters and images jointly using an alternating descent method. This problem is closely related to topics such as compressed sensing, super-resolution, and optimization, which are all sub-categories of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
